<!-- This file wasn't used in the version of RadiKal sector for MV v5.2.3, but now it better be.
Keep building it by moving things to here, and cross fingers.


Enemy ship BLUEPRINTS (not DEFINITIONS) go in autoblueprints.xml.append.

Enemies in events have two components, their BLUEPRINT (which defines the weapons/systems/crew/rooms/etc)
and they also have a ship DEFINITION. This can go in the same file as your other events but 
usually they go in events_ships.xml.append.

SURRENDER events do not, by default, turn the enemy ship neutral.
If you are writing your own surrender event you need to make sure you use the ship tag to make them neutral
in whatever option you include to accept the surrender.
This does mean you can write “fake” surrender events that include some sort of mid-fight event.
Don’t be afraid to get creative.
DJMOD IDEAS: 
- Calling for ASB (which MV probably already does, guards never surrender)
- Start escaping (which MV probably already does)
- Be empowered by enabling/unlimiting systems (which MV probably already does, obelisk/lanius at the Harmony Link,
 and the Lylmik S8 Gate kidnapper from The Outer Expansion)
- Be weakened (limit systems) Might interfere with Punk special combat hacks! (OR disable systems)
- Switch strategies: if was escaping, enable&disable systems to go killmode, and vice-versa.
- Power Surge-type reactions
- Activation of augments, especially one-time use, like AERA Second Wind! Scorched Earth probably too tricky.
- Smaller escape ship: have player choose between scrapping abandoned ship = instant win,
 and chasing = replace current enemy by the smaller one,
 with less loot ("self-destruct timer") but including a valuable item, or crewgain if smaller one can do their own surrender!
 "I really don't wanna die, rather join you"-style dialogue.
- Bigger ship: see above, but enemy "underestimated you and teleports to their REAL ship".
 Player may choose to get low scrap reward and run "before the real ship comes online".
- Steal from you and start escaping, StS-style!


=== EVENT TYPES ===
Events in FTL are typically organized into 6 categories, which are also the eventLists that make up the majority 
of events in a sector. These categories are:

Item Events - these events usually are very peaceful and often generic. They're typically basic free reward events, 
	trade events, or involve some kind of interaction where fighting is undesirable or unlikely.
Neutral Events - these are the second most common type of event in most sectors. They are events which don't have to resolve 
	in a fight but present the player with some option to take a fight.
Distress Events - these are events with a distress beacon.
Quest Events - these are events that have some kind of quest beacon tied to them. Most sectors usually only have 
	at most one or two of these.
Hostile Events - the most generic type of event. Most of these events are very generic "a ship appears, time to fight!" 
	They will usually have mandatory combat, although they might have a niche blue option that gets you out of a fight.
Store Events - in vanilla, these are just extremely generic beacons with a store. In MV however, stores have been reworked 
	to be fully fledged events of their own.

